We start by calculating the two ratios step by step:

1. Gross Profit Margin  
 • Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
 • From the income statement, Gross Profit = 1,620,560.42 and Total Revenue = 2,869,560.42  
 • Calculation = (1,620,560.42 / 2,869,560.42) × 100 ≈ 56.46%

2. Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
 • Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities)  
 • From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -650,630.22  
 • From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 628,478.02  
 • Calculation = -650,630.22 / 628,478.02 ≈ -1.04

Thus, the answer in the specified json format is:

{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '56.46%', 'Operating Cash Flow Ratio': '-1.04'}}
